“On this slide, I’d like to share our upcoming roadmap on hardware traceability.

Starting in April, we will launch a pilot for the hardware return workflow, with a full rollout to all counters in May. A detailed presentation and supporting documentation will be provided next month.

The objective of this first use case is to standardize how hardware returns are handled: ensuring user signature, improving inventory accuracy, and reducing operational effort for support teams.

For users covered by the ITG Group Catalog, this will also bring automation benefits — with requests created instead of incidents, and automatic updates of HLM.

In addition, all return activities processed at counters will now be captured and consolidated in Power BI, giving us full visibility and enabling data-driven analysis.

This is only the first step. We will progressively extend this capability to cover other key use cases:
hardware assignment on request in June, replacement in case of incident in July, and onboarding equipment in September.

Overall, the ambition is to build a fully traceable, standardized, and data-driven hardware lifecycle across all counters.”

